# 2026-05-04 18:06:37.633836
+Read the architecture spec carefully, especially Section 2 (Database Schema) and Section 3 (Folder Structure).
+
+Your task: implement ONLY the Django ORM models and migrations. Nothing else.
+
+---
+
+FOLDER STRUCTURE (strictly follow this):
+
+src/
+
+└─ infrastructure/
+
+   └─ database/
+
+      ├─ models/
+
+      │  ├─ __init__.py
+
+      │  ├─ barber.py
+
+      │  ├─ item.py
+
+      │  ├─ transaction.py
+
+      │  └─ transaction_item.py
+
+      └─ migrations/
+
+---
+
+REQUIREMENTS PER MODEL:
+
+1. barber.py → Table `barbers`
+
+   - id: UUIDField, primary_key=True, default=uuid.uuid4
+
+   - name: CharField(255), not null
+
+   - created_at, updated_at: auto timestamps
+
+2. item.py → Table `items`
+
+   - id: UUIDField, primary_key=True
+
+   - type: CharField(20), choices=['SERVICE','PRODUCT'], not null
+
+   - name: CharField(255), not null
+
+   - price: DecimalField(max_digits=10, decimal_places=2), >= 0
+
+   - stock: IntegerField, default=0, >= 0 (only meaningful for PRODUCT)
+
+   - commission_rate: DecimalField(max_digits=5, decimal_places=4), default=0.0000
+
+   - created_at, updated_at: auto timestamps
+
+3. transaction.py → Table `transactions`
+
+   - id: UUIDField, primary_key=True
+
+   - local_id: CharField(36), UNIQUE, not null  ← idempotency key
+
+   - barber_id: ForeignKey → Barber, not null
+
+   - status: CharField(20), choices=['COMPLETED','VOIDED'], not null
+
+   - discount: DecimalField(max_digits=10, decimal_places=2), default=0.00, >= 0
+
+   - void_reason: TextField, nullable
+
+   - created_at, updated_at: auto timestamps
+
+4. transaction_item.py → Table `transaction_items`
+
+   - id: UUIDField, primary_key=True
+
+   - transaction_id: ForeignKey → Transaction, not null
+
+   - item_id: ForeignKey → Item, not null
+
+   - barber_id: ForeignKey → Barber, not null
+
+   - quantity: IntegerField, not null, > 0
+
+   - price_at_sale: DecimalField(max_digits=10, decimal_places=2), not null, >= 0  ← immutable snapshot
+
+   - commission_rate: DecimalField(max_digits=5, decimal_places=4), not null  ← immutable snapshot
+
+   - created_at: auto timestamp (no updated_at, this table is append-only)
+
+---
+
+INDEXES (add via Meta class):
+
+- transaction_items: composite index on (barber_id, created_at)
+
+- transactions: index on (status)
+
+---
+
+CONSTRAINTS (use CheckConstraint in Meta):
+
+- items.price >= 0
+
+- items.stock >= 0
+
+- items.commission_rate >= 0
+
+- transactions.discount >= 0
+
+- transaction_items.quantity > 0
+
+- transaction_items.price_at_sale >= 0
+
+---
+
+Meta class for all models:
+
+- db_table must match exact table names: 'barbers', 'items', 'transactions', 'transaction_items'
+
+- Use app_label = 'infrastructure' or configure accordingly
+
+---
+
+After creating models:
+
+1. Run `python manage.py makemigrations`
+
+2. Run `python manage.py migrate`
+
+3. Run this verification query via Django shell:
+
+
+
+Output must show ✓ EXISTS for all 4 tables. Do not proceed until verification passes.
+
+---
+
+DO NOT implement:
+
+- Views, URLs, serializers
+
+- Use cases or repositories
+
+- Any business logic
+
+- Admin registration (optional, skip for now)
+
+ONLY models + migrations + verification.

