+1. Exceptions are scattered inconsistently:
+   - Some in modules/*/repositories/exceptions.py
+   - Some in shared/exceptions.py
+   - Duplicate exceptions: BarberNotFound vs BarberNotFoundError, ItemNotFound vs ItemNotFoundError
+
+2. Violates Domain-Driven Design principles where each domain should own its exceptions
+
+Required changes:
+
+1. CREATE a base exception in shared/base_exception.py:
+   \`\`\`python
+   class DomainException(Exception):
+       \"\"\"Base class for all domain exceptions.\"\"\"
+       pass
+   \`\`\`
+
+2. REFACTOR each domain module to have its own exceptions.py at module root (not inside repositories/):
+   - backend/src/modules/catalog/exceptions.py
+   - backend/src/modules/inventory/exceptions.py  
+   - backend/src/modules/sales/exceptions.py
+   - backend/src/modules/staff/exceptions.py
+
+3. MOVE exceptions from repositories/exceptions.py to the new domain exceptions.py files:
+   - ItemNotFound, OutOfStockError → catalog/exceptions.py
+   - StockNotFound, InsufficientStockError → inventory/exceptions.py
+   - TransactionNotFound, CannotVoidTransaction → sales/exceptions.py
+   - BarberNotFound → staff/exceptions.py
+
+4. DELETE the old repository/exceptions.py files
+
+5. UPDATE shared/exceptions.py to ONLY contain DomainException (remove all business exceptions)
+
+6. UPDATE all imports across the codebase:
+   - Change 'from src.modules.catalog.repositories.exceptions import ...' 
+     to 'from src.modules.catalog.exceptions import ...'
+   - Change 'from src.shared.exceptions import ...' to use domain-specific imports
+   - Keep DomainException from shared.base_exception
+
+7. ENSURE naming consistency: all exceptions should end with 'Error' suffix
+   - BarberNotFound → BarberNotFoundError
+   - ItemNotFound → ItemNotFoundError
+   - OutOfStockError is already correct
+   - InsufficientStockError is correct
+   - TransactionNotFound → TransactionNotFoundError
+   - CannotVoidTransaction → CannotVoidTransactionError
