+## Task: Implement Master Data CRUD APIs for Barber and Item management
+
+### Context
+This is a Django + DRF backend for a barbershop POS system. Currently, only checkout, void, and commission report endpoints exist. There are NO endpoints to create/update/delete barbers or items.
+
+### Requirements
+
+#### 1. Create CRUD API for Barbers
+- **Location for interfaces**: `backend/src/modules/staff/repositories/barber_repository.py` (add create/update/delete methods to AbstractBarberRepository)
+- **Location for implementations**: `backend/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/barber_repository.py` (implement new methods)
+- **API endpoints** (in `backend/src/modules/staff/adapters/` - create this folder):
+  - `POST /api/v1/barbers` - Create new barber
+  - `GET /api/v1/barbers` - List all barbers (with pagination: page, per_page)
+  - `GET /api/v1/barbers/{id}` - Get single barber by UUID
+  - `PUT /api/v1/barbers/{id}` - Update barber (full update)
+  - `PATCH /api/v1/barbers/{id}` - Partial update
+  - `DELETE /api/v1/barbers/{id}` - Soft delete (or hard delete? follow existing pattern)
+
+#### 2. Create CRUD API for Items (Services & Products)
+- **Location for interfaces**: `backend/src/modules/catalog/repositories/item_repository.py` (add create/update/delete methods to AbstractItemRepository)
+- **Location for implementations**: `backend/src/infrastructure/database/repositories/item_repository.py` (implement new methods)
+- **API endpoints** (in `backend/src/modules/catalog/adapters/` - create this folder):
+  - `POST /api/v1/items` - Create new item (SERVICE or PRODUCT)
+  - `GET /api/v1/items` - List all items (with filters: type=SERVICE|PRODUCT, pagination)
+  - `GET /api/v1/items/{id}` - Get single item by UUID
+  - `PUT /api/v1/items/{id}` - Update item (full update)
+  - `PATCH /api/v1/items/{id}` - Partial update (e.g., update stock only)
+  - `DELETE /api/v1/items/{id}` - Soft delete (or hard delete? consider transaction_items reference)
+
+#### 3. Serializers
+Create DRF serializers in each adapter folder:
+- `BarberSerializer` with fields: id, name, created_at, updated_at
+- `ItemSerializer` with fields: id, type, name, price, stock, commission_rate, created_at, updated_at
+- Request validation: price >= 0, stock >= 0, commission_rate between 0 and 1
+
+#### 4. URL Configuration
+Update `backend/config/urls.py` to include new routes:
+```python
+path('api/v1/', include('src.modules.staff.adapters.urls')),
+path('api/v1/', include('src.modules.catalog.adapters.urls')),
+5. Exceptions
+Add to existing exception files:
+
+DuplicateNameError (when barber/item name already exists)
+
+InvalidItemTypeError (when type is not SERVICE or PRODUCT)
+
+6. Permissions (Optional but recommended)
+Add basic permission classes:
+
+IsAdminUser for write operations (POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)
+
+IsAuthenticatedOrReadOnly for read operations (GET)
+
+Existing Files to Reference
+backend/src/infrastructure/database/models/barber.py
+
+backend/src/infrastructure/database/models/item.py
+
+backend/src/modules/sales/adapters/views.py (for pattern reference)
+
+backend/src/modules/sales/adapters/serializers.py (for serializer pattern)
+
+backend/src/modules/sales/adapters/urls.py (for URL pattern)
+
+Implementation Order
+First implement Barbers CRUD (simpler)
+
+Then implement Items CRUD
+
+Ensure all endpoints follow the same pattern as existing checkout endpoint
+
+Use Django's transaction.atomic() for write operations
+
+Return proper HTTP status codes (201 for create, 200 for success, 404 for not found, 400 for validation errors)
+
+Example Request/Response
+POST /api/v1/barbers
+Request:
+
+json
+{
+  "name": "John Wick"
+}
+Response (201):
+
+json
+{
+  "id": "uuid",
+  "name": "John Wick",
+  "created_at": "2026-05-07T10:00:00Z",
+  "updated_at": "2026-05-07T10:00:00Z"
+}
+POST /api/v1/items
+Request:
+
+json
