# 2026-05-09 14:55:27.783695
+You are an expert Django developer. Fix the critical bug in my Barbershop POS project.
+
+## Problem
+When creating a checkout transaction, I get this database error:
+null value in column "created_at" of relation "transaction_items" violates not-null constraint
+
+text
+
+## Root Cause
+The `TransactionItem` model has `created_at = models.DateTimeField()` (without default), and the `save_items()` method in `DjangoTransactionRepository` does NOT set `created_at` when bulk creating transaction items.
+
+## Files to Fix
+
+### 1. `src/infrastructure/database/models/transaction_item.py`
+Change the `created_at` field to have a default value using `timezone.now`:
+
+**Current (WRONG):**
+```python
+created_at = models.DateTimeField()
+Should be:
+
+python
+from django.utils import timezone
+created_at = models.DateTimeField(default=timezone.now)
+2. src/infrastructure/database/repositories/transaction_repository.py
+Add created_at=timezone.now() to each TransactionItem when bulk creating:
+
+Current (WRONG):
+
+python
+transaction_items = [
+    TransactionItem(
+        transaction_id=transaction_id,
+        item_id=item["item_id"],
+        barber_id=item["barber_id"],
+        quantity=item["quantity"],
+        price_at_sale=item["price_at_sale"],
+        commission_rate=item["commission_rate"],
+    )
+    for item in items
+]
+Should be:
+
+python
+from django.utils import timezone
+
+transaction_items = [
+    TransactionItem(
+        transaction_id=transaction_id,
+        item_id=item["item_id"],
+        barber_id=item["barber_id"],
+        quantity=item["quantity"],
+        price_at_sale=item["price_at_sale"],
+        commission_rate=item["commission_rate"],
+        created_at=timezone.now(),  # ← ADD THIS
+    )
+    for item in items
+]
+3. Create and apply migration
+After fixing the model, create a new migration:
+
+bash
+python manage.py makemigrations
+python manage.py migrate
+Expected Outcome
+After these changes, the checkout API should work without the created_at null constraint error.
+
+Additional Context
+The test_commission_report.py already sets created_at manually, which is why integration tests passed but real API calls failed.
+
+This is a production-critical bug that prevents any checkout from working.
+
+Make these changes immediately.

