# 2026-05-09 17:16:02.411390
+You are an expert in performance testing. I need to set up load testing for my Django-based Barbershop POS backend using Locust.
+
+## Context
+My project already has:
+- 45+ pytest tests (unit + integration) passing
+- Concurrency tests done with `select_for_update()`
+- Running on Django 5.2 with PostgreSQL
+
+Now I need to test how many concurrent users my API can handle before it breaks.
+
+## Files to Create
+
+### 1. `backend/locustfile.py`
+Create a Locust test file that simulates realistic Barbershop POS user behavior.
+
+**Requirements:**
+- Each user should have a setup phase (`on_start`) that creates or fetches a barber ID, service ID, and product ID
+- Tasks with different weights:
+  - `checkout_mixed_items` (weight 3): Service + product checkout
+  - `checkout_only_product` (weight 2): Product-only checkout
+  - `get_barbers` (weight 1): List barbers
+  - `get_items` (weight 1): List items with type filter
+  - `get_commission_report` (weight 1): Get commission report
+- Use random UUIDs for `local_id` to avoid idempotency conflicts
+- Use `wait_time = between(1, 3)` to simulate human thinking time
+- Include error handling for expected failures (409, 422, 404)
+
+### 2. `backend/scripts/seed_load_test_data.py`
+Create a Django management command to seed test data for load testing.
+
+**Requirements:**
+- Create 1 barber (or reuse existing)
+- Create 1 SERVICE item with high stock (0 stock is fine for services)
+- Create 1 PRODUCT item with LARGE stock (100,000) so it never runs out during load test
+- Print the created IDs for reference
+- Make it idempotent (skip if already exists)
+
+### 3. Update `backend/requirements.txt`
+Add `locust` to the requirements file.
+
+## Expected Commands After Creation:
+
+```bash
+# Seed test data
+python backend/manage.py seed_load_test_data
+
+# Run Locust with Web UI
+cd backend
+locust -f locustfile.py --host=http://localhost:8000
+
+# Run headless stress test
+locust -f locustfile.py --host=http://localhost:8000 \
+  --users=50 --spawn-rate=5 --run-time=2m --headless \
+  --html=reports/load_test_report.html
+
+# Test different loads
+for users in 10 50 100 200 500; do
+  locust -f locustfile.py --host=http://localhost:8000 \
+    --users=$users --spawn-rate=10 --run-time=1m --headless \
+    --html=reports/report_${users}_users.html
+done
+Important Notes:
+The seeding script should be a Django management command, so it can use Django ORM directly
+
+Locust runs OUTSIDE Django, so it makes real HTTP calls
+
+Make sure wait_time is not too low to avoid overwhelming the test server
+
+Include proper exception handling for network errors
+
+The product stock should be large enough to handle all concurrent requests

